summary: @draco9236 -- Worked more on Claudius’ face and hands, and some more on Hamlet’s face as well.  It feels a little slow going...
caption: @draco9236 – Worked more on Claudius’ face and hands, and some more on Hamlet’s face as well.  It feels a little slow going because the reference photo isn’t very high res, so I’m having to just guess on a lot of stuff.  So I hope it looks okay.  XP  The faces are almost done though, other than some tweaking here and there, and I don’t think the hands will be much longer.  The next time consuming bit will probably be detailing the crown, but once that’s done, it should go pretty quickly, as the deep shadows in the clothes make for quick work.  (High contrast tends to be easier to mimic than subtle lighting.)
